The paper deals with distributed algorithms for estimation over multi-agent/sensor networks, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of Kalman filters and information fusion techniques indicates that it could also belong to the categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the focus on estimation and optimization suggests that it could belong to the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
